					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164963" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;" >A Random Day</a></span> <span class="odate time_1456364704 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">25 Feb 2016 01:45</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2462845">
									

<p>The biggest problem I've had with the adventures of Kappa-10 is that everyone follows such well-trodden character beats that it's impossible to be surprised by the characters at all.</p>
<p>This is no different. Grape's backstory is absolutely laden with cliches, from playing <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WarGames">games</a> with a rogue AI to hiding a heart of gold under his vitriolic attitude to being blood brothers with the group's Snake Eyes. I actually rolled my eyes at several points.</p>
<p>But it's also damn well presented and fun to read.</p>

							</div>

								
					
